Block 01 targets a compact 60 GHz LNA on IHP SG13G2 for use as the first public SilicoWeave V-band receive-chain reference block. 
The kickoff objective is to choose an architecture with the highest probability of meeting gain, NF, power, matching, and stability targets after extraction. 
The baseline candidates are two-stage HBT topologies using combinations of common-emitter, CE-CB cascode, and first-stage emitter degeneration. 
No schematic skeleton will be drawn until this document records a justified architecture choice.
